# step to install backend

1. install nodeJS

2. install mongodb "MongoDB Community Server Download" and during
   installation check for mongodb compass install.

3. create folder backend under that run command "npm init" or "npm init -y"
   it will create package.json file.

4. install express which create server & APIs using command "npm install express"

5. install mongoose to connect Node.js with MongoDB usind command "npm install mongoose"

6. install dotenv to Stores sensitive data like DB URL & secret key
   using command "npm install dotenv"

7. install nodemon to Auto-restarts server when you change code
   usind command "npm install nodemon --save-dev"

8. install morgan to usind command "npm install morgan"

9. install bcryptjs to hash passwords (secure storage)
   using command "npm install bcryptjs"
10. install jsonwebtoken to create JWT token for authentication
    using command "npm install jsonwebtoken"
11. install cors for Angular frontend to call backend APIs using command "npm install cors"
12. in package.json file add start under scripts object
    "scripts": {
    "start": "nodemon app.js"
    }
